GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 949
Short Title: School Protection Act. (Public)
Sponsors: Representatives Johnson, Branson, and McNeely (Primary Sponsors).
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Education - K-12, if favorable, Judiciary 2, if favorable, Rules, Calendar, and
Operations of the House
April 14, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO ALLOW SECURITY GUARDS TO CARRY FIREARMS ON NONPUBLIC
3 EDUCATIONAL PROPERTY.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. G.S. 14-269.2(g) is amended by adding a new subdivision to read:
6 "(8) A sworn law enforcement officer who is hired as an armed security guard by
7 a nonpublic school operating under Part I or II of Article 39 of Chapter 115C
8 of the General Statutes, provided that the officer is acting in the discharge of
9 the officer's official duties on the premises of that school. For purposes of this
10 subdivision, a sworn law enforcement officer shall include a sworn law
11 enforcement officer certified under Chapter 17C or 17E of the General
12 Statutes, a company police officer commissioned under Chapter 74E of the
13 General Statutes, or a campus police officer commissioned under Chapter 74G
14 of the General Statutes."
15 SECTION 2. This act becomes effective December 1, 2025, and applies to offenses
16 committed on or after that date.
